{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:psalms.107",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 107,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 107 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:1",
      "text": "O give thanks unto the Lord, for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:2",
      "text": "Let the redeemed of the Lord say so, whom he hath redeemed from the hand of the enemy;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:3",
      "text": "And gathered them out of the lands, from the east, and from the west, from the north, and from the south.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:4",
      "text": "They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way; they found no city to dwell in.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:5",
      "text": "Hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:6",
      "text": "Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:7",
      "text": "And he led them forth by the right way, that they might go to a city of habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:8",
      "text": "Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:9",
      "text": "For he satisfieth the longing soul, and filleth the hungry soul with goodness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:10",
      "text": "Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, being bound in affliction and iron;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:11",
      "text": "Because they rebelled against the words of God, and contemned the counsel of the most High:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:12",
      "text": "Therefore he brought down their heart with labour; they fell down, and there was none to help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:13",
      "text": "Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble, and he saved them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:14",
      "text": "He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and brake their bands in sunder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:15",
      "text": "Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:16",
      "text": "For he hath broken the gates of brass, and cut the bars of iron in sunder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:17",
      "text": "Fools because of their transgression, and because of their iniquities, are afflicted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:18",
      "text": "Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat; and they draw near unto the gates of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:19",
      "text": "Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he saveth them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:20",
      "text": "He sent his word, and healed them, and delivered them from their destructions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:21",
      "text": "Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:22",
      "text": "And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with rejoicing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:23",
      "text": "They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business in great waters;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:24",
      "text": "These see the works of the Lord, and his wonders in the deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:25",
      "text": "For he commandeth, and raiseth the stormy wind, which lifteth up the waves thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:26",
      "text": "They mount up to the heaven, they go down again to the depths: their soul is melted because of trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:27",
      "text": "They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man, and are at their wits’ end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:28",
      "text": "Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble, and he bringeth them out of their distresses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:29",
      "text": "He maketh the storm a calm, so that the waves thereof are still.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:30",
      "text": "Then are they glad because they be quiet; so he bringeth them unto their desired haven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:31",
      "text": "Oh that men would praise the Lord for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:32",
      "text": "Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:33",
      "text": "He turneth rivers into a wilderness, and the watersprings into dry ground;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:34",
      "text": "A fruitful land into barrenness, for the wickedness of them that dwell therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:35",
      "text": "He turneth the wilderness into a standing water, and dry ground into watersprings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:36",
      "text": "And there he maketh the hungry to dwell, that they may prepare a city for habitation;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:37",
      "text": "And sow the fields, and plant vineyards, which may yield fruits of increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.38",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:38",
      "text": "He blesseth them also, so that they are multiplied greatly; and suffereth not their cattle to decrease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.39",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:39",
      "text": "Again, they are minished and brought low through oppression, affliction, and sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.40",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:40",
      "text": "He poureth contempt upon princes, and causeth them to wander in the wilderness, where there is no way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.41",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:41",
      "text": "Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction, and maketh him families like a flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.42",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:42",
      "text": "The righteous shall see it, and rejoice: and all iniquity shall stop her mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.107.43",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:43",
      "text": "Whoso is wise, and will observe these things, even they shall understand the lovingkindness of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
